Constructor Detail

Content

public Content()

Create a new Content instance.

Note that creating a new instance of this object does not upload the Content to the Content Repository.

Content

public Content(java.lang.Long id,
               java.lang.String contentId,
               java.lang.String account,
               java.lang.Long essRequestId,
               java.lang.String author,
               java.util.Date docCreatedDate,
               java.lang.String originalFile,
               java.lang.String format,
               java.lang.Long fileSize,
               java.lang.String title,
               java.util.Date docLastModifiedDate,
               java.lang.String errorMessage,
               java.lang.String securityGroup)

Create a new Content instance with the values passed in.

Note that creating a new instance of this object does not upload the Content to the Content Repository.

Parameters:
id - uniquely identifies a Content in the Content Repository.
contentId - identifies a Content in the Content Repository but not the specific version of the Content. A Content may have many versions as it changes over time.
account - category used to distinguish different groups of Contents.
essRequestId - uniquely identifies an ESS (Enterprise Scheduling System) job.
author - user who uploaded the Content.
docCreatedDate - the date the Content was uploaded.
originalFile - the original name of the Content.
format - the type of the content. For example, plain/text.
fileSize - size of the Content.
title - Content name.
docLastModifiedDate - the date when the Content was modified. This will be the same as the docCreatedDate if the file has not been modified.
errorMessage - only populated if there is an issue interacting with the Content Repository. Provides information as to the nature of the problem being encountered.
securityGroup - name of the security group.

delete

public void delete()
Deletes this Content from the Content Repository.

update

public void update()
Updates this Content in the Content Repository with the process revisionId. The process revisionId is another name for essRequestId. In future, this method may update based on all the fields in the Content not just the essRequestId.
